    <item>
      <title>England water pollution at a 10-year high, campaigners say.</title>
      <link>https://keithpound.com/2025/04/16/england-water-pollution-at-a.html</link>
      <pubDate>Wed, 16 Apr 2025 09:23:17 +0100</pubDate>
      
      <guid>http://KeithPound.micro.blog/2025/04/16/england-water-pollution-at-a.html</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;The number of pollution incidents recorded by water companies in England is at a ten-year high, according to data obtained by campaigners.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Surfers Against Sewage said the Environment Agency data showed the number of incidents was more than double its target.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Such spills have the potential to cause damage to wildlife and illness for people making use of the country&amp;rsquo;s rivers and seas.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Water UK, the industry body representing UK water and sewage companies, said companies plan to invest ¬£12bn to reduce spills by the end of the decade.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/articles/cy5rp6e75q4o&#34;&gt;Read more &amp;hellip;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
    </item>
    
